The UK scientists were also mostly convinced - and many still are - that, once the new virus escaped China, quarantine measures would likely not succeed.
A report from Exeter University, published on February 12, warned a UK outbreak could peak within four months and, without mitigation, infect 45 million people.
For weeks now, doctors and public health workers had been watching out for people with flu-like symptoms coming in from China.
Longley, an infectious diseases consultant at London’s Hospital for Tropical Diseases, was part of a team that staffed a public health service helpline for those with symptoms.
Johnson held out against stringent measures, saying he was following the advice of the government’s scientists.